WEBVTT

00:00.634 --> 00:02.868
Dre: <i>There's a long tradition
of black folks having</i>

00:02.869 --> 00:05.103
<i>an aversion
to doctors and healthcare.</i>

00:05.106 --> 00:07.639
<i>And to be fair, deservedly so...</i>

00:07.641 --> 00:09.608
<i>From overcrowded hospitals,
where black patients</i>

00:09.610 --> 00:13.212
<i>were ignored
by disinterested doctors,</i>

00:13.214 --> 00:15.447
<i>to the Tuskegee experiments,
where white doctors</i>

00:15.449 --> 00:18.617
<i>took way too much interest
in black patients,</i>

00:18.619 --> 00:22.654
<i>treating them like lab rats...
Lab rats with syphilis.</i>

00:22.656 --> 00:24.256
[ Rat squeaks ] <i>By the way
don't be confused.</i>

00:24.258 --> 00:26.792
<i>Tuskegee experiments...
Horrific.</i>

00:26.794 --> 00:29.294
<i>Tuskegee airmen... super-cool.</i>

00:29.296 --> 00:30.662
[ Engine roars ]

00:30.664 --> 00:32.631
<i>The point is,</i>

00:32.632 --> 00:34.599
<i>my parents' generation
always had plenty of reasons</i>

00:34.602 --> 00:37.736
<i>to avoid going to the doctor,
or sending their kids.</i>

00:37.738 --> 00:40.572
I don't feel good.

00:40.574 --> 00:42.408
You're fine.

00:42.410 --> 00:43.742
[ Choking ]

00:43.744 --> 00:45.511
You're fine.
You're fine. You're fine.

00:45.513 --> 00:46.812
[ Groaning ]

00:46.814 --> 00:48.614
Walk it off. You're fine.
[ Groans ]

00:48.616 --> 00:50.449
<i>But I've broken the cycle.</i>

00:50.451 --> 00:52.551
<i>I have a family
who counts on me,</i>

00:52.553 --> 00:54.253
<i>so I take care of myself</i>

00:54.255 --> 00:56.488
<i>by going to the doctor
regularly...</i>

00:57.758 --> 01:00.125
<i>exercising...</i>
Oh!

01:01.462 --> 01:03.529
<i>Watching what I eat...</i>

01:05.399 --> 01:07.099
<i>and getting more sleep.</i>

01:07.101 --> 01:09.201
Now, the key is adding
the long tail...

01:09.203 --> 01:11.837
<i>And I get a physical
every year... no problem.</i>

01:11.839 --> 01:14.473
<i>Except for
the first physical after 40.</i>

01:14.475 --> 01:15.674
Ohh-ohh!

01:15.676 --> 01:17.676
<i>Now, that's a problem.</i>

01:17.678 --> 01:19.478
Come see me in my office.

01:19.480 --> 01:20.546
And clean yourself up.

01:20.548 --> 01:23.248
[ Whimpering ]

01:23.250 --> 01:25.317
♪♪

01:30.524 --> 01:31.657
[ Weakly ] Soup.

01:31.659 --> 01:32.791
Rainbow: What?

01:32.793 --> 01:35.360
So-o-o-o-up.

01:35.362 --> 01:37.529
I'm sorry.
I don't speak "little bitch."

01:37.531 --> 01:39.398
Dre, you don't need soup.

01:39.399 --> 01:41.266
You had a prostate exam.
You're not sick.

01:41.268 --> 01:44.636
I'm not physically sick.
I'm mentally scarred.

01:44.638 --> 01:47.106
That doctor
wore me like a bracelet.

01:47.108 --> 01:48.607
Well, I hope at least
he bought you dinner.

01:48.609 --> 01:50.509
Pops, will you stop riding me?

01:50.511 --> 01:52.444
Now,<i> that's</i> what you should have
said to your doctor.

01:52.446 --> 01:53.812
Bam!
[ Laughs ]

01:53.814 --> 01:55.514
Of all the people,

01:55.516 --> 01:57.883
I thought you would be the
sympathetic one. Mm-hmm.

01:57.885 --> 01:59.685
You know how painful these are.

01:59.687 --> 02:01.386
Guys! Dinner!

02:01.388 --> 02:03.322
Nope. Never had one.

02:03.324 --> 02:05.457
What? The last time I went
to the doctor, it was 1985.

02:05.459 --> 02:06.859
That can't be true.
Oh, yeah.

02:06.861 --> 02:08.594
And I remember
exactly where I was.

02:08.596 --> 02:10.012
I was in a waiting room,

02:10.013 --> 02:11.429
and "we are the world"
came on the radio.

02:11.432 --> 02:14.399
I thought to myself,
"mm, I don't need this [Bleep]"

02:14.401 --> 02:17.202
So is your beef with doctors
or Lionel Richie?

02:17.204 --> 02:18.504
Two snorts of afrin
every morning

02:18.506 --> 02:20.372
has kept me right as rain.

02:20.374 --> 02:22.574
Pops, you know how addictive
that stuff is?

02:22.576 --> 02:23.742
Son, I've been taking afrin

02:23.744 --> 02:25.410
every day for the last 30 years.

02:25.412 --> 02:27.546
I think I would know
if it was addictive.

02:27.548 --> 02:29.615
Besides, don't worry about me.
I'm strong as an ox.

02:29.617 --> 02:31.150
Dumb as one, too.

02:31.152 --> 02:33.185
Hey, who knows where
I can get some potatoes?

02:33.187 --> 02:34.153
Both: Me! I'm a potato!
All right!

02:34.155 --> 02:35.420
Potatoes!

02:35.422 --> 02:37.256
Hey, hey! Careful, pops!
Sack of potatoes!

02:37.258 --> 02:38.390
Careful! Careful!

02:38.392 --> 02:39.892
[ Chuckles ]
Oh, relax.

02:39.894 --> 02:41.393
I've never dropped a child.

02:41.395 --> 02:42.694
Sack of potatoes here!
Get your...

02:42.696 --> 02:44.329
Man: Hey, Earl!

02:44.331 --> 02:46.231
Hey, buddy!

02:46.233 --> 02:48.534
[ Groaning ]

02:48.536 --> 02:50.536
Walk it off.
You're fine.

02:50.538 --> 02:53.705
Besides, I got what they call
old-man strength now.

02:53.707 --> 02:56.208
Yeah,
and old-man smell,

02:56.210 --> 02:58.744
old-man credit,
and old-man balls.

02:58.746 --> 02:59.745
Where are Zoey and junior?

02:59.747 --> 03:01.180
I drove them to the movies.

03:01.182 --> 03:02.648
On a school night?

03:02.650 --> 03:05.784
Since when is Tuesday
a school night?

03:05.786 --> 03:08.654
Ever since people started
going to school.

03:08.656 --> 03:10.455
Eh...
Hey, pops.

03:10.457 --> 03:12.357
Hmm? You really should
get checked out.

03:12.359 --> 03:13.370
Rainbow: You know what?
I'm gonna set you up

03:13.371 --> 03:14.382
with an appointment
at the hospital

03:14.383 --> 03:15.394
so you can get
a quick and easy physical.

03:15.396 --> 03:16.879
Okay, fine.

03:16.880 --> 03:18.363
I'll let one of those butchers
look me over.

03:18.365 --> 03:21.266
Um... You know I'm one
of those butchers, right?

03:21.268 --> 03:22.801
I'm not saying <i>you're</i> a butcher.

03:22.803 --> 03:24.687
Oh, okay.
[ Groans ]

03:24.688 --> 03:26.572
Unless you count
what she did to this meal.

03:26.574 --> 03:27.372
[ Laughter ]

03:27.374 --> 03:28.640
Bam!

03:28.642 --> 03:31.310
♪♪

03:31.312 --> 03:33.478
Come on. See? Look.

03:33.480 --> 03:34.780
There is nothing
to be afraid of, pops.

03:34.782 --> 03:35.981
I'm not scared.
Okay.

03:35.983 --> 03:37.816
Derrick:
I can't taste anything!

03:37.818 --> 03:39.418
What did you do to me?!

03:39.420 --> 03:40.819
What did you do to me?!

03:40.821 --> 03:41.887
I-I think I left something
in my car.

03:41.889 --> 03:42.955
Unh-unh-unh.

03:42.957 --> 03:45.324
I drove. Let's go.

03:45.326 --> 03:46.592
Oh, boy.

03:46.594 --> 03:48.760
[ Groaning ]

03:48.762 --> 03:49.695
I think I left your lights on.

03:49.697 --> 03:51.263
Okay.
Okay, okay, okay.

03:51.265 --> 03:53.498
Oh, oh, look... Evan.
I want you to meet Evan.

03:53.500 --> 03:55.701
This is, uh...
This is my father-in-law.

03:55.703 --> 03:56.735
This is Dr. Windsor.

03:56.737 --> 03:58.403
How's it going?
Not great.

03:58.405 --> 04:00.205
I'm meeting with
my malpractice lawyer.

04:00.207 --> 04:02.541
She's gonna help me run through
my story a few more times.

04:02.543 --> 04:04.543
Okay. All right.
Well, you have a good day, now.

04:04.545 --> 04:05.677
All right.
Goodbye.

04:05.679 --> 04:06.979
No, no, no. Pops, please.
Oh! Pops.

04:06.981 --> 04:07.980
Okay.

04:07.982 --> 04:10.249
Old-man strength...
Very real.

04:10.251 --> 04:11.883
All right.
Can't seem to stop you.

04:11.885 --> 04:13.318
Pops, I'm trying.

04:13.320 --> 04:15.721
The man did not
want to go to the hospital.

04:15.723 --> 04:17.322
He shook bow...

04:17.324 --> 04:18.724
She found him outside
trying to get on the bus.

04:18.726 --> 04:21.026
If he had exact change,
he'd be in Vegas by now.

04:21.028 --> 04:23.012
Well, I don't blame him.

04:23.013 --> 04:24.997
90% of people that step foot
into a hospital die.

04:24.999 --> 04:27.399
You're insane.
And for your information,

04:27.401 --> 04:31.303
100% of people who need to go to
the hospital and don't... Die.

04:31.305 --> 04:32.694
Seriously?

04:32.695 --> 04:34.084
You want to get into
a math-off right now,

04:34.085 --> 04:35.474
while 90% of your dad
is in a hospital, dying?

04:35.476 --> 04:37.192
Josh:
Charlie's got a point.

04:37.193 --> 04:38.909
Step into a hospital over 60...
It's over.

04:38.912 --> 04:40.912
Hospitals are
a young man's game.

04:40.914 --> 04:43.448
Like hopscotch.
Or erections.

04:43.450 --> 04:44.916
I think I know a little
something about medicine.

04:44.918 --> 04:47.319
I've been sleeping
with a doctor for 20 years.

04:47.321 --> 04:48.687
That kind of makes me a doctor.

04:48.689 --> 04:51.140
Oh, so that's how that works.

04:51.141 --> 04:53.592
Well, then I am a bus driver,
a toll-booth operator,

04:53.594 --> 04:55.594
a pbs sign-language
translator,

04:55.596 --> 04:57.062
another
toll-booth operator,

04:57.064 --> 04:58.597
and a sandwich artist.

04:58.599 --> 05:00.932
Mm, well, in that case,
I'm a married college t.A.

05:00.934 --> 05:04.002
Who likes to make a lot of
promises about leaving his wife.

05:04.004 --> 05:07.339
Yet somehow they're having
their fourth kid... Brendan.

05:07.341 --> 05:08.807
I bought him an engraved rattle.

05:08.809 --> 05:10.509
Idiot. Idiot.

05:10.511 --> 05:12.311
Look, the point is, Dre,

05:12.313 --> 05:14.346
is that just like Charlie here

05:14.348 --> 05:15.914
doesn't know how to make
a decent sandwich,

05:15.916 --> 05:18.784
and Lucy is just
a dirty side piece,

05:18.786 --> 05:20.452
you don't know anything
about medicine.

05:20.454 --> 05:22.020
And hospitals <i>are</i> dangerous.

05:22.022 --> 05:25.891
That is why
I have a concierge doctor

05:25.893 --> 05:27.559
who comes to my house
every couple of years

05:27.561 --> 05:29.328
and swaps out my kidneys.

05:29.330 --> 05:31.496
You're only as old
as your organs, Dre.

05:31.498 --> 05:34.633
And right now, I am "drunk teen
motorcyclist" years old.

05:34.635 --> 05:35.801
Josh: Look, Dre,
I get nervous

05:35.803 --> 05:37.069
every time my dad
goes to the hospital.

05:37.071 --> 05:39.571
One time, he went in
for a hip replacement...

05:39.573 --> 05:42.507
Came out an alcoholic
riddled with cancer.

05:42.509 --> 05:44.509
I don't think the hospital
gave your father cancer.

05:44.511 --> 05:47.746
And I definitely don't think
they made him an alcoholic.

05:47.748 --> 05:48.947
[ Gasps ]

05:48.949 --> 05:50.109
You sound just like the jury.

05:51.919 --> 05:54.419
<i>I wasn't going to let those
guys at work spin me out.</i>

05:54.421 --> 05:57.055
<i>They all had old, decrepit dads.</i>

05:57.057 --> 05:59.057
<i>My dad's fine...
Picture of health.</i>

05:59.059 --> 06:01.059
Get out the way!
I've got to hash these browns!

06:01.061 --> 06:03.628
Oh, hey, hey, hey, hey, pops!
Be careful!

06:03.630 --> 06:05.097
He's half of a set!

06:05.099 --> 06:06.665
Hey.
Hmm?

06:06.667 --> 06:09.000
I don't want you to freak out.
Don't freak out.

06:09.002 --> 06:11.136
Pops has a clogged artery.
Don't freak out.

06:11.138 --> 06:13.538
And they think...
Don't freak out...

06:13.540 --> 06:16.508
That he needs a very simple
and routine angioplasty.

06:16.510 --> 06:17.576
Don't freak out.

06:17.578 --> 06:21.813
It's okay.
Don't freak out.

06:21.815 --> 06:24.950
[ Sobbing ] My old,
decrepit pops is gonna die!

06:24.952 --> 06:26.017
[ Sobs ]

06:26.019 --> 06:29.988
[ Weakly ] So-o-o-o-up.

06:33.160 --> 06:34.826
Bow.
Mm-hmm.

06:34.828 --> 06:37.162
I didn't say good night to my pops.
Hmm.

06:37.164 --> 06:39.030
You know, I-i got to say
good night to my pops

06:39.032 --> 06:40.799
while I still can.

06:40.800 --> 06:42.567
How do you say good night
to a man you love?

06:42.569 --> 06:43.702
Good lord, Dre.

06:43.704 --> 06:47.038
Your dad is having
a routine procedure

06:47.040 --> 06:50.008
that has a 95% success rate.

06:50.010 --> 06:51.843
You're right.

06:51.845 --> 06:53.011
I'll say it with a song.

06:53.013 --> 06:55.547
A what?

06:55.549 --> 06:59.851
♪ To dance
with my father again ♪

06:59.853 --> 07:02.788
♪ When I was young ♪

07:02.790 --> 07:04.923
♪ He would lift me up ♪

07:04.925 --> 07:06.525
Ha ha! I got it!

07:06.527 --> 07:08.026
Oh, my god.

07:08.028 --> 07:10.662
So, pops is circling the drain.

07:10.664 --> 07:14.633
No, mom and webmd say balloon
angioplasties are easy.

07:14.635 --> 07:16.535
Balloon?
I want a balloon.

07:16.537 --> 07:18.203
Not in your heart, you don't.

07:18.205 --> 07:20.939
I've never even thought
about losing pops.

07:20.941 --> 07:23.175
Yeah, there's so much
I don't know about him...

07:23.177 --> 07:25.177
So much
I've never thought to ask.

07:25.179 --> 07:28.046
First kiss, secret crush.

07:28.048 --> 07:30.715
Is he pro-choice?
Anti-fracking?

07:30.717 --> 07:32.584
And where is he on seaworld?

07:32.586 --> 07:35.587
It's up to me
to record his life story.

07:35.589 --> 07:38.623
When pops dies,
what happens to all his stuff?

07:38.625 --> 07:40.091
They'll probably just
throw it all away.

07:40.093 --> 07:42.027
You know our parents
are animals.

07:42.029 --> 07:43.562
They can't do that.

07:43.564 --> 07:46.998
I know. The '70s are
coming back strong. Yes.

07:47.000 --> 07:47.866
Jack and Zoey:
I get the brown hat.

07:47.868 --> 07:48.900
Not if I get it first.

07:48.902 --> 07:51.937
Please. I'm smaller.

07:51.939 --> 07:54.673
I'm everywhere and nowhere.

07:54.675 --> 07:58.009
I have no idea what that means,
but it's on.

07:58.011 --> 07:59.211
Diane:
Look at yourselves!

07:59.213 --> 08:01.780
You guys are focusing
on the wrong thing.

08:01.782 --> 08:02.914
You're right.
Sorry.

08:02.916 --> 08:04.015
Thank you.

08:04.017 --> 08:08.053
The real prize
is power of attorney.

08:08.055 --> 08:09.921
♪♪

08:09.923 --> 08:11.590
Ow.

08:11.592 --> 08:14.593
Bow, I tried singing to him,
and he took a swing at me.

08:14.595 --> 08:15.994
Barely connected.

08:15.996 --> 08:19.664
He...
He's really slowing down.

08:19.666 --> 08:21.500
Aw.

08:21.502 --> 08:23.268
Dre.

08:23.270 --> 08:26.938
I'm so sorry
your dad didn't hit you.

08:26.940 --> 08:28.507
For so many reasons.

08:28.509 --> 08:30.542
It's weird.

08:30.544 --> 08:33.211
I always thought of pops
as being invincible.

08:33.213 --> 08:35.197
I know. I know.

08:35.198 --> 08:37.182
It is so hard
to see our parents get older.

08:37.184 --> 08:39.017
I mean,
I called my mom this week.

08:39.019 --> 08:40.519
She told me the same story

08:40.521 --> 08:42.854
that she's told me
three times, Dre.

08:42.856 --> 08:44.022
Three times.

08:44.024 --> 08:46.224
Wow.
I know. Oh, my god.

08:46.226 --> 08:50.028
You know, you've told me
that story twice.

08:50.030 --> 08:51.162
Twice.

08:51.164 --> 08:53.265
♪♪

08:55.002 --> 08:57.002
Ruby:
A little bacon for you.

08:57.004 --> 08:59.638
A little bacon for you.

08:59.640 --> 09:00.839
A little bacon for my baby.

09:00.841 --> 09:03.008
And...

09:03.010 --> 09:04.510
Bacon.

09:04.511 --> 09:06.011
Oh, I know you're
trying to kill me with it.

09:06.013 --> 09:07.245
But that's all right.
I don't care.

09:07.247 --> 09:08.647
Mmm.

09:08.649 --> 09:10.982
Death by pork...
A warrior's death.

09:10.984 --> 09:12.250
Rainbow:
Good morning, everybody!

09:12.252 --> 09:16.555
Real bacon.
And... and pancakes?

09:16.557 --> 09:18.690
Ruby, I told you
I don't like the kids

09:18.692 --> 09:20.191
eating a sugary breakfast
on a school day.

09:20.193 --> 09:22.260
Since when is Thursday
a school day?

09:22.262 --> 09:25.263
Besides, I have a right
to spoil my grandbabies.

09:25.265 --> 09:26.598
Now, who wants ice cream?

09:26.600 --> 09:27.666
I do! I do!
Me!

09:27.668 --> 09:28.867
[ Laughs ]

09:28.869 --> 09:31.636
Why, why are you the sick one?

09:31.638 --> 09:33.305
I'm not sick.
Okay.

09:33.307 --> 09:34.606
Zoey: Yeah, mom.
Don't worry about pops.

09:34.608 --> 09:37.342
He's gonna live forever.

09:37.344 --> 09:38.944
Oh, thank you, Zo-Zo.

09:38.946 --> 09:40.579
Junior:
Hey, pops, man,

09:40.581 --> 09:43.782
you have some great sayings...
Uh, "crabs in a barrel."

09:43.784 --> 09:46.117
Mm. Eat your biggest
crabs first.

09:46.119 --> 09:48.653
What would you say is your
favorite crab-based saying?

09:48.655 --> 09:50.922
Hmm.
Strictly crab-based.

09:50.924 --> 09:52.290
Mm-hmm.

09:52.292 --> 09:54.125
Well, you led off
with two very strong ones there.

09:54.127 --> 09:56.161
Um, I'd have...

09:56.163 --> 09:58.263
Boy, what... are you recording
me for posterity?

09:58.265 --> 10:00.165
Well...

10:00.167 --> 10:02.167
Boy, you better turn that thing
off and take your ass to school

10:02.169 --> 10:04.603
before I flip you
like a cross-tailed crab!

10:04.605 --> 10:06.838
[ Sighs ]

10:06.840 --> 10:09.774
So much crab wisdom.
So little time.

10:09.776 --> 10:11.977
I'm sorry
he's so insensitive, pops.

10:11.979 --> 10:14.613
Will you please sign
this permission slip

10:14.615 --> 10:15.914
for a school trip.

10:15.916 --> 10:17.182
Oh. Of course,
baby girl.

10:17.184 --> 10:18.917
♪♪

10:20.954 --> 10:22.120
There you go.

10:22.122 --> 10:24.055
Thank you.
You're welcome.

10:24.057 --> 10:26.057
Y'all have a good day at
school, now, hear? All right.

10:26.059 --> 10:27.092
Bye, babies.

10:27.094 --> 10:29.794
Now all we need to do
is scan this

10:29.796 --> 10:30.929
and e-mail it
to his lawyer.

10:30.931 --> 10:32.030
Cool.

10:32.032 --> 10:33.898
Whoo!
Good morning, everybody.

10:33.900 --> 10:35.767
Good morning, baby boy.

10:35.769 --> 10:36.935
What you doing with my suitcase?

10:36.937 --> 10:38.136
I'm moving you
out of the guest house

10:38.138 --> 10:39.404
into one of our spare bedrooms

10:39.406 --> 10:41.773
so we can keep an eye on you
while you recuperate.

10:41.775 --> 10:44.275
I don't need to recuperate.
I'm not having any operation.

10:44.277 --> 10:45.710
What?

10:45.712 --> 10:48.847
I got a second opinion.
And I'm fine.

10:48.849 --> 10:49.914
Angioplasty?
Yeah.

10:49.916 --> 10:51.282
Man, naw.

10:51.284 --> 10:53.351
You walked up here, didn't you?
On my own two feet.

10:53.353 --> 10:55.203
Oh, you good.

10:55.204 --> 10:57.054
If it feels real bad,
use a little afrin.

10:57.057 --> 10:58.957
That helps.
I've been doing that every day.

10:58.959 --> 11:00.792
I got some liniment
in the truck for 5 bucks.

11:00.794 --> 11:02.327
Also got bath towels...
2 for $8.

11:02.329 --> 11:04.963
Liniment?
Afrin?

11:04.965 --> 11:06.865
You guys are crazy.
[ Chuckles ]

11:06.867 --> 11:09.801
Cranberry juice.
Cleanses the blood.

11:09.803 --> 11:12.370
So I'm good.
You...

11:12.372 --> 11:15.140
Cranberry juice is for
urinary-tract infection.

11:15.142 --> 11:16.675
It's not gonna help your heart.

11:16.677 --> 11:19.077
And that's some very pale
cranberry juice.

11:19.079 --> 11:20.278
That's 'cause it's mostly gin.

11:20.280 --> 11:22.147
What...

11:22.149 --> 11:23.248
Mm. Give me a swallow of that.

11:23.250 --> 11:24.315
Hey, hey.

11:24.317 --> 11:26.685
She shot you
the last time she had gin.

11:26.687 --> 11:28.887
♪♪

11:28.889 --> 11:30.722
Good morning, gentlemen.

11:30.724 --> 11:31.990
What are the haps?

11:31.992 --> 11:34.459
Whoa, Dre.
A two-muffin morning?

11:34.461 --> 11:36.995
What has got you down?

11:36.997 --> 11:39.330
My pops won't get
the angioplasty.

11:39.332 --> 11:42.167
An old-timer at my barbershop
is going through the same thing.

11:42.169 --> 11:44.035
Just tell him to drink
a little cranberry juice.

11:44.037 --> 11:46.004
Why is everybody talking
about cranberry juice?

11:46.006 --> 11:48.206
Cranberry juice
doesn't do anything.

11:48.208 --> 11:51.076
I've got to go
make a phone call.

11:51.078 --> 11:53.178
Josh: Dre, you got to make him
get that procedure.

11:53.180 --> 11:54.946
The time's come for you
to step up

11:54.948 --> 11:57.082
and be a dad to your dad
like I do.

11:57.083 --> 11:59.217
I mean, I got to change my old
man's diaper every other day.

11:59.219 --> 12:01.086
Every other day?

12:01.088 --> 12:03.021
Well, you should have seen
how he parented me.

12:03.023 --> 12:05.090
Payback's a bitch.

12:05.092 --> 12:07.225
Stevens: Dre, I-i know that we
put you off hospitals yesterday,

12:07.227 --> 12:08.927
but this is no joke.

12:08.929 --> 12:11.096
You don't want your father
to die of arteriosclerosis,

12:11.098 --> 12:12.797
like my father.

12:12.799 --> 12:14.966
He keeled over in a field.

12:14.968 --> 12:18.303
At least he died as he lived...
Picking onions in a dress.

12:18.305 --> 12:20.338
Hmm.

12:20.340 --> 12:22.373
I miss you, paw-maw.

12:22.375 --> 12:26.010
♪♪

12:26.012 --> 12:28.480
[<i> Gunfire</i> ]
Junior: [ Laughing ] Stop!

12:28.482 --> 12:29.981
Hey, guys.

12:29.983 --> 12:31.316
Die, Hitler!

12:31.318 --> 12:34.018
What?! Jack?!
Hey!

12:34.020 --> 12:35.136
You know you're not allowed

12:35.137 --> 12:36.253
to play with
those violent video games.

12:36.256 --> 12:37.922
Grandma said it was okay.

12:37.924 --> 12:39.491
Ruby!

12:39.493 --> 12:44.129
You don't want the boy
to learn killing Nazis is good?

12:44.131 --> 12:46.097
Strange message, rainbow.

12:46.099 --> 12:48.099
♪♪

12:48.101 --> 12:50.935
Oh, hey.
Love you, pops.

12:50.937 --> 12:52.003
Oh, love you, too,
Zo-Zo.

12:52.005 --> 12:53.505
[ Door closes ]

12:53.507 --> 12:56.341
All right, pops.

12:56.343 --> 12:57.342
Hey.
Enough of this.

12:57.344 --> 12:58.877
Hey.

12:58.879 --> 13:01.063
I was watching "scandal."

13:01.064 --> 13:03.248
Well, if you want to live
to see Olivia have Fitz's baby,

13:03.250 --> 13:04.366
you're gonna get that surgery.

13:04.367 --> 13:05.483
Don't waste your breath.
I'm not getting it.

13:05.485 --> 13:06.818
Hey.

13:06.820 --> 13:08.453
Yes, you are.

13:08.455 --> 13:12.090
Boy, I'm<i> your</i> father.
You don't tell me what to do.

13:12.092 --> 13:13.324
I just did!

13:13.326 --> 13:15.143
What?

13:15.144 --> 13:16.961
Why didn't you tell him
about the 90% success rate?

13:16.963 --> 13:18.229
I thought you said it was 95%.

13:18.231 --> 13:19.430
Eh...

13:19.432 --> 13:21.466
Who wants pizza?
Ooh.

13:21.468 --> 13:24.536
What's your favorite pizza?
Most memorable topping?

13:24.538 --> 13:27.405
Where were you when you first
tasted Chicago deep-dish?

13:27.407 --> 13:28.973
Chicago, idiot.

13:28.975 --> 13:31.509
I will always Cherish this.

13:31.511 --> 13:33.945
Jack: You know what I like
on my pizza?

13:33.947 --> 13:35.079
Potatoes!
That's funny.

13:35.081 --> 13:36.948
I just bought
a fresh sack of 'em.

13:36.950 --> 13:39.284
Come on.
Get your potatoes here.

13:39.286 --> 13:41.119
Fresh, hot pot... [
Gasping ] Ruby: Earl!

13:41.121 --> 13:42.204
Pops!
Earl!

13:42.205 --> 13:43.288
Hey, hey, hey, hey!
What's going on, pops?

13:43.290 --> 13:44.455
Everything okay?
What happened?

13:44.457 --> 13:46.157
Everything's fine.
Okay.

13:46.158 --> 13:47.858
Everything's fine.
I'll have the damn operation.

13:47.861 --> 13:49.194
But not because of you.

13:49.196 --> 13:52.030
I'll let one of them quacks
cut me open.

13:52.032 --> 13:53.765
Oh, they actually
don't cut you open.

13:53.766 --> 13:55.499
They just make a little small
incision in your groin,

13:55.502 --> 13:57.302
and then they have
a-a metal tube...

13:57.304 --> 13:59.004
Yeah, but he... he...
He said he'll have it.

13:59.005 --> 14:00.705
That they feed all the way up
he... he said he'll have it.

14:00.706 --> 14:02.406
He's gonna have... okay. You
already said yes. Yeah.

14:02.409 --> 14:04.943
So I'm just gonna stop talking
and I'm gonna book it.

14:04.945 --> 14:05.944
Stop... stop...
Stop talking.

14:05.946 --> 14:09.080
Okay, pops. Sit.
Hoo.

14:09.082 --> 14:11.549
[ Breathing heavily ]
You happy now?

14:11.551 --> 14:13.184
♪♪

14:18.491 --> 14:19.624
Hey.
Hey.

14:19.626 --> 14:20.959
So, I took the day off work,

14:20.960 --> 14:22.293
and your mom said she can pick the
kids up from school. No, no, no.

14:22.295 --> 14:23.428
That's okay.

14:23.430 --> 14:24.246
You...
You don't have to go.

14:24.247 --> 14:25.063
Pops is gonna be fine.

14:25.065 --> 14:26.364
I know he'll be fine.

14:26.366 --> 14:29.300
The procedure has
an 88% success rate.

14:29.302 --> 14:30.401
I thought you said 90%.

14:30.403 --> 14:31.402
Can we stay focused, please?

14:31.404 --> 14:33.037
Okay.
I'm worried about you.

14:33.039 --> 14:34.005
Me?
Yes.

14:34.007 --> 14:35.340
I'm great.
All right?

14:35.342 --> 14:36.908
Pops is doing the right thing.

14:36.910 --> 14:37.942
This is good.

14:37.944 --> 14:38.643
Yes, it is.

14:38.645 --> 14:39.878
Andre, son.

14:39.880 --> 14:41.179
Yeah?

14:41.181 --> 14:44.315
Uh, come on and take a walk
with me.

14:44.317 --> 14:46.117
[ Diddy and faith Evans'
"I'll be missing you" plays ]

14:46.119 --> 14:47.185
[ Door opens ]

14:50.523 --> 14:52.624
This isn't right.

14:52.626 --> 14:54.926
<i>That's when it hit me...</i>

14:54.928 --> 14:57.028
<i>Pops wanted to take this walk</i>

14:57.030 --> 15:00.265
<i>because he thought it might be
our last walk.</i>

15:00.267 --> 15:01.966
<i>He was scared.</i>

15:01.968 --> 15:04.535
<i>But maybe this was
an opportunity,</i>

15:04.537 --> 15:08.006
<i>our chance to say all the
things we hadn't said before.</i>

15:08.008 --> 15:10.008
Hmm?
Son, son.

15:10.010 --> 15:11.476
Dog poop.

15:11.478 --> 15:13.578
[ Chuckles ]

15:13.580 --> 15:15.313
Thanks, pops.

15:15.315 --> 15:16.948
Anytime.

15:16.950 --> 15:20.985
♪ Every step I take ♪

15:20.987 --> 15:23.922
♪ Every move I make ♪ oh, hey, pops,
you want to take another lap?

15:23.924 --> 15:25.390
Yeah, I'd like that.

15:25.392 --> 15:27.292
♪ Every single day ♪

15:27.294 --> 15:29.394
♪ Every time I pray ♪

15:29.396 --> 15:32.597
♪ I'll be missing you ♪

15:32.599 --> 15:34.132
Rainbow.
Yes.

15:34.134 --> 15:36.000
I want you to know
that I trust you.

15:36.002 --> 15:37.135
And I love you.

15:37.137 --> 15:39.237
Thank you, pops.
I love you, too.

15:39.239 --> 15:41.339
Hey, pops.
There's another hand over here.

15:41.341 --> 15:42.540
[ Grunting ] And I want you to
be in the operating room with me

15:42.542 --> 15:43.942
when I go under.

15:43.944 --> 15:45.009
Just knowing that you're there

15:45.011 --> 15:46.494
will give me great comfort.

15:46.495 --> 15:47.978
I will be there with you.
I will be there.

15:47.981 --> 15:49.380
Orderly: We need to
take you in now.

15:49.382 --> 15:50.448
Go ahead. You're okay.
Okay, pops, let me go.

15:50.449 --> 15:51.515
Just let me go, pops!
Okay.

15:51.518 --> 15:54.018
Oh. Damn that
old-man strength!

15:54.020 --> 15:55.286
Hey, pops!

15:55.288 --> 15:56.955
Don't forget to breathe!
Oh. Don't say that.

15:56.957 --> 15:58.056
Don't say that? Okay. No.

15:58.058 --> 15:59.357
Uh, meet you on the other side!

15:59.359 --> 16:01.326
Not that, either.
The other side of the doors.

16:01.328 --> 16:02.694
No, no, no... it sounds weird.
Okay.

16:02.696 --> 16:04.128
Hey.

16:04.130 --> 16:04.696
Aren't you gonna go in there?

16:04.698 --> 16:06.197
No. No.

16:06.199 --> 16:08.199
Can't.
A zillion protocols against it.

16:08.201 --> 16:09.300
What...

16:09.301 --> 16:10.400
Just tell them
what they want to hear.

16:10.403 --> 16:11.669
[ Chuckles ]

16:11.671 --> 16:14.505
You people really are monsters.

16:14.507 --> 16:15.974
I know.
We're awful.

16:15.976 --> 16:17.308
But, you know,
we need to cultivate

16:17.310 --> 16:18.943
a healthy sense of detachment.

16:18.944 --> 16:20.577
Plus, I'm not gonna get
all worked up over a procedure

16:20.580 --> 16:22.413
that has an 85% survival rate.

16:22.415 --> 16:24.282
85%?
[ Cellphone chimes ]

16:24.284 --> 16:26.150
Does anybody survive
these things?

16:26.152 --> 16:27.352
Oh, no.
What?

16:27.354 --> 16:29.988
It's Ruby.
Diane threw up.

16:29.990 --> 16:31.155
She wants me to come home.

16:31.157 --> 16:33.691
You okay
if I leave you here by yourself?

16:33.693 --> 16:36.127
Oh, yeah, yeah. You know,
I'd be better without you.

16:36.129 --> 16:37.528
Rea...
You sociopath.

16:37.530 --> 16:38.696
Mm-hmm.
I love you, too.

16:38.698 --> 16:40.331
Oh, do you?
I do.

16:40.333 --> 16:41.533
Okay.
I love you.

16:41.534 --> 16:42.734
I know you're scared.
You're okay.

16:42.736 --> 16:44.202
Yeah, all right.
It's gonna be good.

16:44.204 --> 16:45.303
Okay.
It is.

16:45.305 --> 16:46.270
Just...
You think so?

16:46.272 --> 16:47.505
Just keep breathing, sweetie.

16:47.507 --> 16:49.640
[ Inhales raggedly ]
Yeah, there you go.

16:49.642 --> 16:50.775
[ Exhales deeply ]

16:53.613 --> 16:55.246
You know, he's fine.
He's fine.

16:55.248 --> 16:57.081
E-ever... everything...
Everything's gonna be fine.

16:57.083 --> 16:59.584
He's...
He's gonna be okay.

16:59.586 --> 17:03.354
Am... am I boring you,
or you don't speak English?

17:03.356 --> 17:04.555
Both.

17:04.557 --> 17:06.524
Oh, I'm sorry.
I'll leave you be.

17:06.526 --> 17:07.658
I mean, you know,
what can go wrong?

17:07.660 --> 17:09.293
It's just
a simple balloon angioplas...

17:09.295 --> 17:10.795
[ balloon pops ]
[ Gasps, screaming ]

17:10.797 --> 17:13.064
Oh, my daddy's dead!

17:13.066 --> 17:14.549
My daddy's dead

17:14.550 --> 17:16.033
and I didn't get a chance
to tell him I loved him!

17:16.036 --> 17:17.468
Now it's too late!

17:17.470 --> 17:20.705
Damn, damn, damn chains.

17:20.707 --> 17:22.140
Excuse me?
Aah!

17:22.142 --> 17:23.708
Mr. Johnson?
Yes, doctor?

17:23.709 --> 17:25.275
Your father's procedure's
finished, and he's doing great.

17:25.278 --> 17:26.811
What?! Oh! Ahh!

17:26.813 --> 17:28.646
Mwah!
Thank you, doctor!

17:28.648 --> 17:31.115
Ahh!

17:31.117 --> 17:34.452
He's alive, despite the odds!

17:34.454 --> 17:35.620
Okay.
All right.

17:35.622 --> 17:37.321
I just want to let you know

17:37.323 --> 17:39.457
that all your loved ones
is gonna be okay, all right?

17:39.459 --> 17:41.125
Well,
you know, maybe not all of them.

17:41.127 --> 17:42.393
It<i> is</i> a hospital.
[ Chuckles ]

17:42.395 --> 17:44.262
Hey, little man.
Sorry about your balloon.

17:44.264 --> 17:46.330
Uh, Selena?
<i>Vaya con dios.</i>

17:46.332 --> 17:49.534
Mm-hmm.
My daddy all right!

17:49.536 --> 17:51.135
My daddy all right!

17:52.539 --> 17:54.305
Is she okay?

17:54.307 --> 17:55.640
She's gonna be fine.

17:55.642 --> 17:58.643
[ Sighs ]
This is all on me, bow.

17:58.645 --> 18:00.078
I never should have let her

18:00.080 --> 18:02.280
chase the milkshake with churros

18:02.282 --> 18:05.183
and a fast pony ride
in the heat.

18:06.219 --> 18:08.686
I spoil 'em too much, bow.

18:08.688 --> 18:09.821
I'm a bad grandma.

18:09.823 --> 18:11.789
No, Ruby, you're a bad person.

18:11.791 --> 18:13.124
Hey.

18:13.126 --> 18:15.760
But you are a fantastic grandma.

18:15.762 --> 18:17.395
It's okay that you spoil them.

18:17.397 --> 18:21.365
I mean... Every moment we get
with you is a gift.

18:21.367 --> 18:23.768
[ Cellphone chimes ]
Oh.

18:23.770 --> 18:25.336
Oh, pops is out.

18:25.338 --> 18:27.371
He's doing great.
Oh, thank god he's okay.

18:27.373 --> 18:28.539
He's okay.
He's okay.

18:28.541 --> 18:29.740
He's okay.
He's okay.

18:29.742 --> 18:31.876
But you...
You're in trouble.

18:31.878 --> 18:32.877
What?

18:32.879 --> 18:34.712
[ Laughs ]
You called me a gift.

18:34.714 --> 18:36.147
No.

18:36.149 --> 18:38.216
And I am never gonna let you
forget it.

18:38.218 --> 18:40.551
Okay, no, no.
I-i was worried about pops.

18:40.553 --> 18:41.586
I was in emotional distress.
♪ I am a gift ♪

18:41.588 --> 18:42.787
Okay, you're a gift.

18:42.789 --> 18:45.189
♪ I am a gift ♪
Ruby.

18:45.191 --> 18:47.325
♪ I am a gift ♪ I also
called you a bad person.

18:47.327 --> 18:48.526
No, I'm a gift!

18:48.527 --> 18:49.726
No, you're a...
No, I'm a gift!

18:49.729 --> 18:51.796
You are a bad per... very bad.
♪ I'm a gift ♪

18:51.798 --> 18:54.165
[ Monitor beeping ]

18:59.239 --> 19:02.373
Can't close my eyes
for a minute.

19:02.375 --> 19:04.442
Oh, you're awake.

19:04.444 --> 19:06.310
You made it.

19:06.312 --> 19:08.146
Hmm.
Not that I was worried.

19:08.148 --> 19:09.280
Oh, no.

19:09.282 --> 19:10.615
No. Me either.

19:10.617 --> 19:12.383
Hmm.

19:12.385 --> 19:14.285
I-I'm lying, pops.

19:14.287 --> 19:15.586
Man, I was terrified.

19:15.588 --> 19:18.289
'Cause you're soft,
like a crab in summer.

19:18.291 --> 19:20.258
[ Both laugh ]
Ruby: Knock, knock.

19:20.260 --> 19:22.727
Quit circling, vulture.
I'm still alive.

19:22.729 --> 19:26.230
Don't be a jackass, jackass.

19:26.232 --> 19:28.633
I'm glad to see you finally
taking care of yourself.

19:28.635 --> 19:31.569
Mm. I want to be the
favorite grandparent...

19:31.571 --> 19:32.803
Not the only one.

19:32.805 --> 19:34.572
Aww.
Listen at you.

19:34.574 --> 19:35.439
Thank you, Ruby.

19:35.441 --> 19:38.242
Aww.

19:38.244 --> 19:40.478
Least I can do.

19:40.480 --> 19:41.913
Get some rest, now.

19:45.418 --> 19:46.951
Wow.

19:46.953 --> 19:49.220
That was nice.

19:49.222 --> 19:50.955
Yeah, sure was, wasn't it?

19:50.957 --> 19:53.591
Mm-hmm.

19:55.428 --> 19:57.361
Heifer stole my Vicodin!

19:57.363 --> 19:58.596
Mama! What you talking
about "mama"?

19:58.598 --> 20:00.431
You tried to steal
my damn pudding.

20:00.433 --> 20:02.153
Well, hell, I didn't want
that cold chicken.

20:03.937 --> 20:04.902
Okay.

20:04.904 --> 20:07.438
[ Both laugh ]

20:07.440 --> 20:08.773
I'mma eat it.
[ Laughs ]

20:11.945 --> 20:13.477
All right.

20:13.479 --> 20:15.947
Hey, pops, the doctor said
you've got to be active.

20:15.949 --> 20:17.448
All right.
All right, come on.

20:17.450 --> 20:19.350
Come on.
Let's move it a little bit.

20:19.352 --> 20:20.751
[ Grunting ] Okay. Hold
onto me for balance.

20:20.753 --> 20:22.253
[ Groans ]
There you go.

20:22.255 --> 20:23.321
Okay. There you go. Come on.
Let's go.

20:23.323 --> 20:24.823
Let's go.
Okay.

20:24.824 --> 20:26.324
A little to the left.
To the left.

20:26.326 --> 20:27.792
A little to the right.
A little to the right.

20:27.794 --> 20:28.826
How you feeling?
Feeling good?

20:28.828 --> 20:30.595
Yeah, I'm okay.
Okay, hold on.

20:30.597 --> 20:32.964
Let me see that app.
Mm.

20:32.966 --> 20:34.398
[ Luther vandross' "dance with
my father" plays ] Mm-hmm.

20:34.400 --> 20:37.235
Oh, hell, no.
[ Laughs ]

20:37.237 --> 20:39.738
Oh, see, I know what happened.

20:39.739 --> 20:42.240
What? I died on the table.
Now I'm in hell.

20:42.242 --> 20:43.909
Come on, come on, come on.
Let's stretch it out.

20:43.910 --> 20:45.577
See, you always trying to lead.
Stretch it out.

20:45.578 --> 20:47.245
♪ If I could get another chance
♪ there you go. Come on.

20:47.247 --> 20:48.779
Turn around.
Ohh, ohh, ohh.

20:48.781 --> 20:50.381
Real good.
Ohh.

20:50.383 --> 20:53.517
♪ Another walk ♪
uh-huh. Okay.

20:53.519 --> 20:56.387
♪ Another dance with him ♪ come on.
You know you love this.

20:56.389 --> 20:59.457
You know you love this. ♪ I'd play a
song that would never, ever end ♪

20:59.459 --> 21:01.492
There you go. Come on, dad.
[ Laughs ]

21:01.494 --> 21:03.327
♪ How I'd love, love, love ♪
get ready for the dip.

21:03.329 --> 21:05.596
Ohh, ohh, ohh, ohh!
Oh!

21:05.598 --> 21:08.933
♪ To dance with my father again ♪ oh!
Help me up!

21:08.935 --> 21:10.935
[ Groaning ]

21:10.937 --> 21:13.638
Oh!

21:13.640 --> 21:15.640
♪ Ooh-ooh-ooh ♪ I think
I pulled my back out.

21:15.642 --> 21:18.042
Oh.

21:18.044 --> 21:19.710
Whoo! Whoo!

21:19.712 --> 21:21.912
[ Both laugh ]
